# Commit message template following the repository's AGENTS.md (Conventional Commits)
# Header: type(scope?): subject
# - type: feat, fix, perf, docs, style, refactor, test, chore, build, ci, revert
# - scope: optional, short noun (e.g., canvas, gauge)
# - subject: short imperative summary (max ~72 chars)
# Examples:
#   feat(canvas): add export as PNG
#   fix(gauge): correct rounding in calculation

type(scope?): subject

# Body (optional): motivation and contrast. Wrap at ~72 chars.
#
# Footer (optional):
# - Use `BREAKING CHANGE: description` for breaking API changes (or type! in header).
# - Reference issues when applicable: `Closes #123`

# Notes:
# - Keep the header short and imperative.
# - Use scopes to make the changelog clearer (e.g., feat(canvas): ...).
